{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1610,"text":"When you have 21 minutes to speak,"},{"time":3595,"text":"two million years seems\nlike a really long time."},{"time":6595,"text":"But evolutionarily,\ntwo million years is nothing."},{"time":9065,"text":"And yet in two million years,"},{"time":11042,"text":"the human brain\nhas nearly tripled in mass,"},{"time":14821,"text":"going from the one-and-a-quarter pound\nbrain of our ancestor here, Habilis,"},{"time":19054,"text":"to the almost three-pound meatloaf"},{"time":20840,"text":"that everybody here\nhas between their ears."},{"time":24512,"text":"What is it about a big brain"},{"time":27931,"text":"that nature was so eager\nfor every one of us to have one?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31712,"text":"Well, it turns out when\nbrains triple in size,"},{"time":33971,"text":"they don't just get three times bigger;\nthey gain new structures."},{"time":37510,"text":"And one of the main reasons our brain got\nso big is because it got a new part,"},{"time":42420,"text":"called the \"frontal lobe.\""},{"time":43776,"text":"Particularly, a part called\nthe \"pre-frontal cortex.\""},{"time":46893,"text":"What does a pre-frontal cortex\ndo for you that should justify"},{"time":50360,"text":"the entire architectural overhaul\nof the human skull"},{"time":53964,"text":"in the blink of evolutionary time?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":55751,"text":"It turns out the pre-frontal\ncortex does lots of things,"},{"time":58791,"text":"but one of the most important things\nit does is an experience simulator."},{"time":64705,"text":"Pilots practice in flight simulators"},{"time":67057,"text":"so that they don't make\nreal mistakes in planes."},{"time":69997,"text":"Human beings have this\nmarvelous adaptation"},{"time":72617,"text":"that they can actually have\nexperiences in their heads"},{"time":76386,"text":"before they try them out in real life."},{"time":78601,"text":"This is a trick that none\nof our ancestors could do,"},{"time":81148,"text":"and that no other animal\ncan do quite like we can."},{"time":84413,"text":"It's a marvelous adaptation."},{"time":85967,"text":"It's up there with opposable thumbs\nand standing upright and language"},{"time":89858,"text":"as one of the things that got\nour species out of the trees"},{"time":93302,"text":"and into the shopping mall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95479,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":97415,"text":"All of you have done this."},{"time":98719,"text":"Ben and Jerry's doesn't have\nliver-and-onion ice cream,"},{"time":102576,"text":"and it's not because they whipped\nsome up, tried it and went, \"Yuck.\""},{"time":106008,"text":"It's because, without\nleaving your armchair,"},{"time":109054,"text":"you can simulate that flavor\nand say \"yuck\" before you make it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115652,"text":"Let's see how your experience\nsimulators are working."},{"time":118248,"text":"Let's just run a quick diagnostic"},{"time":120111,"text":"before I proceed\nwith the rest of the talk."},{"time":122273,"text":"Here's two different futures\nthat I invite you to contemplate."},{"time":126012,"text":"You can try to simulate them and tell me\nwhich one you think you might prefer."},{"time":130062,"text":"One of them is winning the lottery.\nThis is about 314 million dollars."},{"time":135620,"text":"And the other is becoming paraplegic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138524,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":139566,"text":"Just give it a moment of thought."},{"time":141218,"text":"You probably don't feel\nlike you need a moment of thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144053,"text":"Interestingly, there are data\non these two groups of people,"},{"time":148195,"text":"data on how happy they are."},{"time":150197,"text":"And this is exactly\nwhat you expected, isn't it?"},{"time":153240,"text":"But these aren't the data.\nI made these up!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156038,"text":"These are the data."},{"time":157714,"text":"You failed the pop quiz, and you're hardly\nfive minutes into the lecture."},{"time":161234,"text":"Because the fact is that a year\nafter losing the use of their legs,"},{"time":165430,"text":"and a year after winning the lotto,\nlottery winners and paraplegics"},{"time":170181,"text":"are equally happy with their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173356,"text":"Don't feel too bad\nabout failing the first pop quiz,"},{"time":175836,"text":"because everybody fails\nall of the pop quizzes all of the time."},{"time":179795,"text":"The research that my laboratory\nhas been doing,"},{"time":182208,"text":"that economists and psychologists\naround the country have been doing,"},{"time":185565,"text":"has revealed something\nreally quite startling to us,"},{"time":188385,"text":"something we call the \"impact bias,\""},{"time":190254,"text":"which is the tendency\nfor the simulator to work badly."},{"time":193795,"text":"For the simulator to make you\nbelieve that different outcomes"},{"time":198018,"text":"are more different\nthan in fact they really are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200401,"text":"From field studies to laboratory studies,"},{"time":202708,"text":"we see that winning or losing an election,\ngaining or losing a romantic partner,"},{"time":207471,"text":"getting or not getting a promotion,\npassing or not passing a college test,"},{"time":211322,"text":"on and on, have far less impact,\nless intensity and much less duration"},{"time":217244,"text":"than people expect them to have."},{"time":221014,"text":"This almost floors me --"},{"time":226085,"text":"a recent study showing\nhow major life traumas affect people"},{"time":230595,"text":"suggests that if it happened\nover three months ago,"},{"time":233595,"text":"with only a few exceptions,"},{"time":235181,"text":"it has no impact whatsoever\non your happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239798,"text":"Why?"},{"time":241488,"text":"Because happiness can be synthesized."},{"time":245145,"text":"Sir Thomas Brown wrote in 1642,\n\"I am the happiest man alive."},{"time":249455,"text":"I have that in me that can convert poverty\nto riches, adversity to prosperity."},{"time":254595,"text":"I am more invulnerable than Achilles;\nfortune hath not one place to hit me.\""},{"time":259565,"text":"What kind of remarkable machinery\ndoes this guy have in his head?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":262778,"text":"Well, it turns out it's precisely the same\nremarkable machinery that all off us have."},{"time":268775,"text":"Human beings have something"},{"time":270663,"text":"that we might think of\nas a \"psychological immune system.\""},{"time":273928,"text":"A system of cognitive processes, largely\nnon-conscious cognitive processes,"},{"time":278945,"text":"that help them change\ntheir views of the world,"},{"time":282403,"text":"so that they can feel better"},{"time":283824,"text":"about the worlds\nin which they find themselves."},{"time":286776,"text":"Like Sir Thomas, you have this machine."},{"time":288666,"text":"Unlike Sir Thomas,\nyou seem not to know it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293486,"text":"We synthesize happiness, but we think\nhappiness is a thing to be found."},{"time":298595,"text":"Now, you don't need me to give you"},{"time":300293,"text":"too many examples of people\nsynthesizing happiness, I suspect."},{"time":304405,"text":"Though I'm going to show\nyou some experimental evidence,"},{"time":307053,"text":"you don't have to look\nvery far for evidence."},{"time":309221,"text":"I took a copy of the New York Times"},{"time":310916,"text":"and tried to find some instances\nof people synthesizing happiness."},{"time":314124,"text":"Here are three guys\nsynthesizing happiness."},{"time":316161,"text":"\"I'm better off physically,\nfinancially, mentally ..."},{"time":318866,"text":"\"I don't have one minute's regret.\nIt was a glorious experience.\""},{"time":321939,"text":"\"I believe it turned out for the best.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":323894,"text":"Who are these characters\nwho are so damn happy?"},{"time":326167,"text":"The first one is Jim Wright."},{"time":327561,"text":"Some of you are old enough to remember:"},{"time":329456,"text":"he was the chairman\nof the House of Representatives"},{"time":331943,"text":"and he resigned in disgrace"},{"time":333339,"text":"when this young Republican\nnamed Newt Gingrich"},{"time":335518,"text":"found out about a shady\nbook deal he had done."},{"time":337686,"text":"He lost everything."},{"time":338952,"text":"The most powerful Democrat\nin the country lost everything."},{"time":341754,"text":"He lost his money, he lost his power."},{"time":343574,"text":"What does he have to say\nall these years later?"},{"time":345886,"text":"\"I am so much better off physically,\nfinancially, mentally"},{"time":348649,"text":"and in almost every other way.\""},{"time":350474,"text":"What other way would there\nbe to be better off?"},{"time":352737,"text":"Vegetably? Minerally? Animally?"},{"time":354589,"text":"He's pretty much covered them there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357327,"text":"Moreese Bickham is somebody\nyou've never heard of."},{"time":359832,"text":"Moreese Bickham uttered\nthese words upon being released."},{"time":362536,"text":"He was 78 years old."},{"time":363869,"text":"He'd spent 37 years\nin a Louisiana State Penitentiary"},{"time":366816,"text":"for a crime he didn't commit."},{"time":368324,"text":"[He was ultimately released"},{"time":370181,"text":"for good behavior\nhalfway through his sentence.]"},{"time":372474,"text":"What did he say about his experience?"},{"time":374474,"text":"\"I don't have one minute's regret.\nIt was a glorious experience.\" Glorious!"},{"time":378056,"text":"He is not saying,"},{"time":379330,"text":"\"Well, there were some nice guys.\nThey had a gym.\""},{"time":381750,"text":"\"Glorious,\""},{"time":382925,"text":"a word we usually reserve for something\nlike a religious experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386227,"text":"Harry S. Langerman uttered these words,\nand he's somebody you might have known"},{"time":389980,"text":"but didn't, because in 1949\nhe read a little article in the paper"},{"time":393613,"text":"about a hamburger stand owned\nby two brothers named McDonalds."},{"time":396603,"text":"And he thought,\n\"That's a really neat idea!\""},{"time":398858,"text":"So he went to find them. They said,"},{"time":400565,"text":"\"We can give you a franchise\non this for 3,000 bucks.\""},{"time":403133,"text":"Harry went back to New York,\nasked his brother, an investment banker,"},{"time":406397,"text":"to loan him the $3,000,\nand his brother's immortal words were,"},{"time":409329,"text":"\"You idiot, nobody eats hamburgers.\""},{"time":411071,"text":"He wouldn't lend him the money,"},{"time":412584,"text":"and of course, six months later\nRay Kroc had exactly the same idea."},{"time":415822,"text":"It turns out people do eat hamburgers,"},{"time":418040,"text":"and Ray Kroc, for a while,\nbecame the richest man in America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421864,"text":"And then, finally,"},{"time":423046,"text":"some of you recognize\nthis young photo of Pete Best,"},{"time":426530,"text":"who was the original\ndrummer for the Beatles,"},{"time":428697,"text":"until they, you know, sent him\nout on an errand and snuck away"},{"time":432546,"text":"and picked up Ringo on a tour."},{"time":434530,"text":"Well, in 1994, when Pete Best\nwas interviewed --"},{"time":436850,"text":"yes, he's still a drummer;\nyes, he's a studio musician --"},{"time":439910,"text":"he had this to say: \"I'm happier\nthan I would have been with the Beatles.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":443441,"text":"Okay. There's something important\nto be learned from these people,"},{"time":446597,"text":"and it is the secret of happiness."},{"time":448496,"text":"Here it is, finally to be revealed."},{"time":450893,"text":"First: accrue wealth, power,\nand prestige, then lose it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454139,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":456815,"text":"Second: spend as much of your life\nin prison as you possibly can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460597,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":461622,"text":"Third: make somebody else\nreally, really rich."},{"time":464876,"text":"And finally: never ever join the Beatles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467623,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":468671,"text":"Yeah, right."},{"time":469846,"text":"Because when people synthesize happiness,"},{"time":471956,"text":"as these gentlemen seem to have done,"},{"time":474174,"text":"we all smile at them,\nbut we kind of roll our eyes and say,"},{"time":477977,"text":"\"Yeah right, you never\nreally wanted the job.\""},{"time":480537,"text":"\"Oh yeah, right. You really didn't have\nthat much in common with her,"},{"time":484537,"text":"and you figured that out just\nabout the time"},{"time":486657,"text":"she threw the engagement\nring in your face.\""},{"time":488777,"text":"We smirk because we believe\nthat synthetic happiness"},{"time":492537,"text":"is not of the same quality\nas what we might call \"natural happiness.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":496037,"text":"What are these terms?"},{"time":497513,"text":"Natural happiness is what we get\nwhen we get what we wanted,"},{"time":500941,"text":"and synthetic happiness is what we make\nwhen we don't get what we wanted."},{"time":505869,"text":"And in our society,\nwe have a strong belief"},{"time":508869,"text":"that synthetic happiness\nis of an inferior kind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511869,"text":"Why do we have that belief?"},{"time":513900,"text":"Well, it's very simple."},{"time":515598,"text":"What kind of economic engine\nwould keep churning"},{"time":519415,"text":"if we believed\nthat not getting what we want"},{"time":522375,"text":"could make us just as happy as getting it?"},{"time":525844,"text":"With all apologies\nto my friend Matthieu Ricard,"},{"time":528971,"text":"a shopping mall full of Zen monks"},{"time":531197,"text":"is not going to be\nparticularly profitable,"},{"time":533335,"text":"because they don't want stuff enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535961,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537066,"text":"I want to suggest to you\nthat synthetic happiness"},{"time":540187,"text":"is every bit as real and enduring"},{"time":542416,"text":"as the kind of happiness you stumble upon"},{"time":545091,"text":"when you get exactly\nwhat you were aiming for."},{"time":547678,"text":"I'm a scientist, so I'm going\nto do this not with rhetoric,"},{"time":550478,"text":"but by marinating you\nin a little bit of data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552653,"text":"Let me first show you an experimental\nparadigm that is used"},{"time":555623,"text":"to demonstrate the synthesis of happiness\namong regular old folks."},{"time":559829,"text":"And this isn't mine."},{"time":561011,"text":"It's a 50-year-old paradigm\ncalled the \"free choice paradigm.\""},{"time":564011,"text":"It's very simple."},{"time":565416,"text":"You bring in, say, six objects,"},{"time":568146,"text":"and you ask a subject to rank them\nfrom the most to the least liked."},{"time":571431,"text":"In this case, because\nthis experiment uses them,"},{"time":574013,"text":"these are Monet prints."},{"time":575416,"text":"So, everybody can rank these Monet prints"},{"time":577416,"text":"from the one they like the most,\nto the one they like the least."},{"time":580441,"text":"Now we give you a choice:"},{"time":582155,"text":"\"We happen to have\nsome extra prints in the closet."},{"time":584581,"text":"We're going to give you\none as your prize to take home."},{"time":587226,"text":"We happen to have number three\nand number four,\" we tell the subject."},{"time":591082,"text":"This is a bit of a difficult choice,"},{"time":593004,"text":"because neither one is preferred\nstrongly to the other,"},{"time":595630,"text":"but naturally, people\ntend to pick number three"},{"time":598274,"text":"because they liked it\na little better than number four."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601764,"text":"Sometime later -- it could be\n15 minutes; it could be 15 days --"},{"time":605308,"text":"the same stimuli are put\nbefore the subject,"},{"time":607416,"text":"and the subject is asked\nto re-rank the stimuli."},{"time":610145,"text":"\"Tell us how much you like them now.\""},{"time":612146,"text":"What happens?"},{"time":613377,"text":"Watch as happiness is synthesized."},{"time":615370,"text":"This is the result that has\nbeen replicated over and over again."},{"time":618416,"text":"You're watching happiness be synthesized."},{"time":620431,"text":"Would you like to see it again?"},{"time":623023,"text":"Happiness!"},{"time":624416,"text":"\"The one I got is really\nbetter than I thought!"},{"time":626679,"text":"That other one I didn't get sucks!\""},{"time":628416,"text":"That's the synthesis of happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630583,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631644,"text":"Now, what's the right response to that?"},{"time":634717,"text":"\"Yeah, right!\""},{"time":637334,"text":"Now, here's the experiment we did,"},{"time":639416,"text":"and I hope this is going to convince you"},{"time":641355,"text":"that \"Yeah, right!\"\nwas not the right response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643656,"text":"We did this experiment\nwith a group of patients"},{"time":645902,"text":"who had anterograde amnesia."},{"time":647323,"text":"These are hospitalized patients."},{"time":649006,"text":"Most of them have Korsakoff's syndrome,"},{"time":651195,"text":"a polyneuritic psychosis."},{"time":653955,"text":"They drank way too much,\nand they can't make new memories."},{"time":657416,"text":"OK? They remember their childhood,\nbut if you walk in and introduce yourself,"},{"time":661353,"text":"and then leave the room,"},{"time":662570,"text":"when you come back,\nthey don't know who you are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665979,"text":"We took our Monet prints to the hospital."},{"time":669392,"text":"And we asked these patients to rank them"},{"time":672416,"text":"from the one they liked\nthe most to the one they liked the least."},{"time":675536,"text":"We then gave them the choice\nbetween number three and number four."},{"time":679416,"text":"Like everybody else, they said,"},{"time":681416,"text":"\"Gee, thanks Doc! That's great!\nI could use a new print."},{"time":684107,"text":"I'll take number three.\""},{"time":685860,"text":"We explained we would have\nnumber three mailed to them."},{"time":689416,"text":"We gathered up our materials\nand we went out of the room,"},{"time":692416,"text":"and counted to a half hour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693803,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":694828,"text":"Back into the room,\nwe say, \"Hi, we're back.\""},{"time":698336,"text":"The patients, bless them,\nsay, \"Ah, Doc, I'm sorry,"},{"time":701416,"text":"I've got a memory problem;\nthat's why I'm here."},{"time":704177,"text":"If I've met you before, I don't remember.\""},{"time":706202,"text":"\"Really, you don't remember?\nI was just here with the Monet prints?\""},{"time":709418,"text":"\"Sorry, Doc, I just don't have a clue.\""},{"time":712036,"text":"\"No problem, Jim. All I want\nyou to do is rank these for me"},{"time":715678,"text":"from the one you like the most\nto the one you like the least.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":719798,"text":"What do they do?"},{"time":720973,"text":"Well, let's first check and make sure\nthey're really amnesiac."},{"time":723903,"text":"We ask these amnesiac patients\nto tell us which one they own,"},{"time":727917,"text":"which one they chose last\ntime, which one is theirs."},{"time":731239,"text":"And what we find is amnesiac\npatients just guess."},{"time":734416,"text":"These are normal controls,\nwhere if I did this with you,"},{"time":737076,"text":"all of you would know\nwhich print you chose."},{"time":739203,"text":"But if I do this with amnesiac patients,\nthey don't have a clue."},{"time":743031,"text":"They can't pick\ntheir print out of a lineup."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746825,"text":"Here's what normal controls do:\nthey synthesize happiness."},{"time":750416,"text":"Right? This is the change in liking score,"},{"time":752999,"text":"the change from the first time they ranked\nto the second time they ranked."},{"time":756530,"text":"Normal controls show --\nthat was the magic I showed you;"},{"time":759233,"text":"now I'm showing it to you\nin graphical form --"},{"time":761416,"text":"\"The one I own is better than I thought."},{"time":763577,"text":"The one I didn't own,\nthe one I left behind,"},{"time":765966,"text":"is not as good as I thought.\""},{"time":768520,"text":"Amnesiacs do exactly the same thing.\nThink about this result."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773027,"text":"These people like better the one they own,"},{"time":775861,"text":"but they don't know they own it."},{"time":779526,"text":"\"Yeah, right\" is not the right response!"},{"time":783885,"text":"What these people did\nwhen they synthesized happiness"},{"time":787091,"text":"is they really, truly changed"},{"time":789750,"text":"their affective, hedonic, aesthetic\nreactions to that poster."},{"time":795003,"text":"They're not just saying it\nbecause they own it,"},{"time":797416,"text":"because they don't know they own it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800688,"text":"When psychologists show you bars,"},{"time":803339,"text":"you know that they are showing\nyou averages of lots of people."},{"time":806918,"text":"And yet, all of us have this\npsychological immune system,"},{"time":810251,"text":"this capacity to synthesize happiness,"},{"time":812749,"text":"but some of us do this trick\nbetter than others."},{"time":815924,"text":"And some situations allow anybody\nto do it more effectively"},{"time":819981,"text":"than other situations do."},{"time":823321,"text":"It turns out that freedom,"},{"time":826590,"text":"the ability to make up your mind\nand change your mind,"},{"time":829940,"text":"is the friend of natural happiness,\nbecause it allows you to choose"},{"time":833519,"text":"among all those delicious futures"},{"time":835719,"text":"and find the one\nthat you would most enjoy."},{"time":838226,"text":"But freedom to choose,"},{"time":840002,"text":"to change and make up your mind,"},{"time":841783,"text":"is the enemy of synthetic happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844729,"text":"And I'm going to show you why.\nDilbert already knows, of course."},{"time":847799,"text":"\"Dogbert's tech support.\nHow may I abuse you?\""},{"time":850005,"text":"\"My printer prints a blank\npage after every document.\""},{"time":852643,"text":"\"Why complain about getting free paper?\""},{"time":854643,"text":"\"Free? Aren't you just\ngiving me my own paper?\""},{"time":856943,"text":"\"Look at the quality of the free paper\ncompared to your lousy regular paper!"},{"time":860643,"text":"Only a fool or a liar would say\nthat they look the same!\""},{"time":863443,"text":"\"Now that you mention it,\nit does seem a little silkier!\""},{"time":866229,"text":"\"What are you doing?\""},{"time":867429,"text":"\"I'm helping people accept the things\nthey cannot change.\" Indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871775,"text":"The psychological immune system works best"},{"time":874125,"text":"when we are totally stuck,\nwhen we are trapped."},{"time":877344,"text":"This is the difference\nbetween dating and marriage."},{"time":879750,"text":"You go out on a date with a guy,"},{"time":881343,"text":"and he picks his nose;\nyou don't go out on another date."},{"time":884003,"text":"You're married to a guy\nand he picks his nose?"},{"time":886201,"text":"He has a heart of gold.\nDon't touch the fruitcake!"},{"time":888707,"text":"You find a way to be happy\nwith what's happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":892444,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":893469,"text":"Now, what I want to show you"},{"time":894882,"text":"is that people don't know\nthis about themselves,"},{"time":897509,"text":"and not knowing this can work\nto our supreme disadvantage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901811,"text":"Here's an experiment we did at Harvard."},{"time":903812,"text":"We created a black-and-white\nphotography course,"},{"time":906864,"text":"and we allowed students to come in\nand learn how to use a darkroom."},{"time":910343,"text":"So we gave them cameras;\nthey went around campus;"},{"time":912701,"text":"they took 12 pictures\nof their favorite professors"},{"time":915082,"text":"and their dorm room and their dog,"},{"time":917296,"text":"and all the other things they wanted\nto have Harvard memories of."},{"time":920438,"text":"They bring us the camera;\nwe make up a contact sheet;"},{"time":922988,"text":"they figure out which are\nthe two best pictures;"},{"time":925307,"text":"and we now spend six hours\nteaching them about darkrooms."},{"time":928013,"text":"And they blow two of them up,"},{"time":929478,"text":"and they have two gorgeous\neight-by-10 glossies"},{"time":931748,"text":"of meaningful things to them, and we say,"},{"time":933756,"text":"\"Which one would you like to give up?\""},{"time":935620,"text":"\"I have to give one up?\""},{"time":936795,"text":"\"Yes, we need one as evidence\nof the class project."},{"time":939931,"text":"So you have to give me one.\nYou have to make a choice."},{"time":942573,"text":"You get to keep one,\nand I get to keep one.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":945343,"text":"Now, there are two conditions\nin this experiment."},{"time":948343,"text":"In one case, the students are told,"},{"time":950645,"text":"\"But you know,\nif you want to change your mind,"},{"time":953025,"text":"I'll always have the other one here,"},{"time":954902,"text":"and in the next four days, before\nI actually mail it to headquarters\" --"},{"time":959289,"text":"Yeah, \"headquarters\" --"},{"time":961638,"text":"\"I'll be glad to swap it out with you."},{"time":964343,"text":"In fact, I'll come to your dorm room,\njust give me an email."},{"time":967337,"text":"Better yet, I'll check with you."},{"time":969352,"text":"You ever want to change your mind,\nit's totally returnable.\""},{"time":972264,"text":"The other half of the students\nare told exactly the opposite:"},{"time":975185,"text":"\"Make your choice, and by the way,"},{"time":976836,"text":"the mail is going out, gosh,\nin two minutes, to England."},{"time":979853,"text":"Your picture will be winging\nits way over the Atlantic."},{"time":982599,"text":"You will never see it again.\""},{"time":984789,"text":"Half of the students\nin each of these conditions"},{"time":987067,"text":"are asked to make predictions"},{"time":988503,"text":"about how much they're going to come\nto like the picture that they keep"},{"time":992138,"text":"and the picture they leave behind."},{"time":993843,"text":"Other students are just sent back\nto their little dorm rooms"},{"time":996774,"text":"and they are measured\nover the next three to six days"},{"time":999909,"text":"on their liking, satisfaction\nwith the pictures."},{"time":1002208,"text":"And look at what we find."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1003424,"text":"First of all, here's what students\nthink is going to happen."},{"time":1006572,"text":"They think they're going to maybe\ncome to like the picture they chose"},{"time":1010396,"text":"a little more\nthan the one they left behind,"},{"time":1012909,"text":"but these are not statistically\nsignificant differences."},{"time":1015993,"text":"It's a very small increase,\nand it doesn't much matter"},{"time":1019681,"text":"whether they were in the reversible\nor irreversible condition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022673,"text":"Wrong-o. Bad simulators. Because\nhere's what's really happening."},{"time":1026909,"text":"Both right before the swap\nand five days later,"},{"time":1030330,"text":"people who are stuck with that picture,"},{"time":1032540,"text":"who have no choice,"},{"time":1033716,"text":"who can never change their mind,"},{"time":1035780,"text":"like it a lot!"},{"time":1037934,"text":"And people who are deliberating\n-- \"Should I return it?"},{"time":1040909,"text":"Have I gotten the right one?\nMaybe this isn't the good one?"},{"time":1044148,"text":"Maybe I left the good one?\" --\nhave killed themselves."},{"time":1046764,"text":"They don't like their picture,"},{"time":1048225,"text":"and in fact even after the opportunity\nto swap has expired,"},{"time":1051082,"text":"they still don't like their picture."},{"time":1053199,"text":"Why?"},{"time":1054373,"text":"Because the [reversible] condition\nis not conducive"},{"time":1058392,"text":"to the synthesis of happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060164,"text":"So here's the final piece\nof this experiment."},{"time":1063076,"text":"We bring in a whole new group\nof naive Harvard students"},{"time":1066909,"text":"and we say, \"You know,\nwe're doing a photography course,"},{"time":1070289,"text":"and we can do it one of two ways."},{"time":1072607,"text":"We could do it so that when\nyou take the two pictures,"},{"time":1075162,"text":"you'd have four days to change your mind,"},{"time":1077185,"text":"or we're doing another course\nwhere you take the two pictures"},{"time":1080082,"text":"and you make up your mind right away\nand you can never change it."},{"time":1083189,"text":"Which course would you like\nto be in?\" Duh!"},{"time":1085259,"text":"66 percent of the students, two-thirds,"},{"time":1087909,"text":"prefer to be in the course where they have\nthe opportunity to change their mind."},{"time":1091909,"text":"Hello? 66 percent of the students\nchoose to be in the course"},{"time":1095909,"text":"in which they will ultimately be deeply\ndissatisfied with the picture."},{"time":1099909,"text":"Because they do not know the conditions\nunder which synthetic happiness grows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1106747,"text":"The Bard said everything best,\nof course, and he's making my point here"},{"time":1111861,"text":"but he's making it hyperbolically:"},{"time":1113909,"text":"\"'Tis nothing good or bad /\nBut thinking makes it so.\""},{"time":1116909,"text":"It's nice poetry,\nbut that can't exactly be right."},{"time":1120372,"text":"Is there really nothing good or bad?"},{"time":1122909,"text":"Is it really the case that gall bladder\nsurgery and a trip to Paris"},{"time":1126282,"text":"are just the same thing?"},{"time":1127917,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1129028,"text":"That seems like a one-question IQ test."},{"time":1132909,"text":"They can't be exactly the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134909,"text":"In more turgid prose,\nbut closer to the truth,"},{"time":1137909,"text":"was the father of modern capitalism,\nAdam Smith, and he said this."},{"time":1141307,"text":"This is worth contemplating:"},{"time":1143286,"text":"\"The great source of both the misery\nand disorders of human life"},{"time":1147262,"text":"seems to arise from overrating\nthe difference"},{"time":1149909,"text":"between one permanent\nsituation and another --"},{"time":1152909,"text":"Some of these situations may, no doubt,\ndeserve to be preferred to others,"},{"time":1158230,"text":"but none of them can deserve to be pursued"},{"time":1161183,"text":"with that passionate ardor\nwhich drives us to violate the rules"},{"time":1165651,"text":"either of prudence or of justice,"},{"time":1168270,"text":"or to corrupt the future\ntranquility of our minds,"},{"time":1171059,"text":"either by shame from the remembrance\nof our own folly,"},{"time":1174620,"text":"or by remorse for the horror\nof our own injustice.\""},{"time":1178716,"text":"In other words: yes, some things\nare better than others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1183472,"text":"We should have preferences that lead us\ninto one future over another."},{"time":1188999,"text":"But when those preferences\ndrive us too hard and too fast"},{"time":1192804,"text":"because we have overrated\nthe difference between these futures,"},{"time":1196519,"text":"we are at risk."},{"time":1198512,"text":"When our ambition is bounded,\nit leads us to work joyfully."},{"time":1202821,"text":"When our ambition is unbounded,"},{"time":1204717,"text":"it leads us to lie, to cheat,\nto steal, to hurt others,"},{"time":1209155,"text":"to sacrifice things of real value."},{"time":1211178,"text":"When our fears are bounded,"},{"time":1213219,"text":"we're prudent, we're cautious,"},{"time":1215378,"text":"we're thoughtful."},{"time":1216613,"text":"When our fears\nare unbounded and overblown,"},{"time":1219872,"text":"we're reckless, and we're cowardly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1222625,"text":"The lesson I want to leave\nyou with, from these data,"},{"time":1225999,"text":"is that our longings and our worries\nare both to some degree overblown,"},{"time":1230102,"text":"because we have within us the capacity\nto manufacture the very commodity"},{"time":1236298,"text":"we are constantly chasing\nwhen we choose experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1240741,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1241916,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}